1
00:01:13,720 --> 00:01:19,840
Let them go.

2
00:01:19,840 --> 00:01:21,240
What are you yelling for?

3
00:01:21,240 --> 00:01:21,840
What are you yelling for?

4
00:01:21,840 --> 00:01:23,320
Why are you arresting people?

5
00:01:23,320 --> 00:01:24,250
On what grounds?

6
00:01:25,680 --> 00:01:28,539
Because you are gathering to disturb public order.

7
00:01:31,920 --> 00:01:33,080
Disturb public order?

8
00:01:33,080 --> 00:01:34,680
Have we done anything like stealing

9
00:01:34,680 --> 00:01:36,039
or thieving?

10
00:01:36,160 --> 00:01:37,039
I think it's you.

11
00:01:37,039 --> 00:01:37,960
You...

12
00:01:37,960 --> 00:01:39,640
You are afraid that our patriotic salvation movement

13
00:01:39,640 --> 00:01:40,479
will one day

14
00:01:40,479 --> 00:01:42,800
become a resistance movement, aren't you?

15
00:01:42,800 --> 00:01:44,039
Refuse to be enslaved!

16
00:01:44,039 --> 00:01:46,240
Unite and drive out the invaders!

17
00:01:46,240 --> 00:01:47,440
Refuse to be enslaved!

18
00:01:47,440 --> 00:01:49,520
Unite and drive out the invaders!

19
00:01:49,600 --> 00:01:50,840
Drive out the invaders!

20
00:01:50,840 --> 00:01:52,100
Refuse to be enslaved!

21
00:01:52,440 --> 00:01:53,570
If you keep yelling,

22
00:01:53,759 --> 00:01:55,160
I'll arrest all of you!

23
00:01:56,280 --> 00:01:58,360
Arrest us! Arrest me too if you dare!

24
00:02:33,480 --> 00:02:37,600
All members of the Wuhan Choir have unanimously decided

25
00:02:37,600 --> 00:02:40,860
that all performance proceeds will go to disaster relief.

26
00:03:31,160 --> 00:03:31,960
Lin Yaozu.

27
00:03:34,720 --> 00:03:36,180
Did you do that on purpose?

28
00:03:37,160 --> 00:03:38,079
I've been looking for you for a long time.

29
00:03:38,079 --> 00:03:39,410
I thought you were lost.

30
00:03:39,920 --> 00:03:41,400
I didn't expect you to be so smart.

31
00:03:41,400 --> 00:03:43,160
You even knew to find the police.

32
00:03:43,160 --> 00:03:44,600
I just asked a passerby.

33
00:03:44,600 --> 00:03:46,400
He told me to go to the police if I need help.

34
00:03:46,400 --> 00:03:48,040
So I asked my way here.

35
00:03:48,720 --> 00:03:50,240
I saw you standing here for a long time.

36
00:03:50,240 --> 00:03:51,840
Did you remember something?

37
00:03:56,640 --> 00:03:57,720
Back in our time,

38
00:03:57,720 --> 00:03:59,250
the police were too fierce.

39
00:03:59,400 --> 00:04:00,280
So...

40
00:04:01,280 --> 00:04:03,640
Our police today are not like that.

41
00:04:03,720 --> 00:04:04,240
Now,

42
00:04:04,240 --> 00:04:06,320
we all call them Uncle Police.

43
00:04:06,440 --> 00:04:09,000
Last time my second aunt's cat got lost,

44
00:04:09,000 --> 00:04:10,920
Uncle Police helped find it.

45
00:04:13,040 --> 00:04:14,400
The police help find cats?

46
00:04:14,400 --> 00:04:15,200
Yes.

47
00:04:20,399 --> 00:04:21,320
Let's go.

48
00:04:21,320 --> 00:04:22,920
For example, if you lose something else,

49
00:04:22,920 --> 00:04:24,600
you can also ask the police to help you find it.

50
00:04:24,600 --> 00:04:26,000
Like a lost wallet.

51
00:04:29,520 --> 00:04:30,800
This street is not bad.

52
00:04:32,920 --> 00:04:34,320
There seems to be a lot of food ahead.

53
00:04:34,320 --> 00:04:35,320
Let's go taste it.

54
00:04:35,520 --> 00:04:36,600
Hey handsome,

55
00:04:36,720 --> 00:04:39,120
buy a bouquet for these two pretty ladies.

56
00:04:39,760 --> 00:04:41,000
No need, thanks.

57
00:04:41,920 --> 00:04:44,250
Please do me a favor and make my first sale.

58
00:04:46,040 --> 00:04:46,920
Look,

59
00:04:46,920 --> 00:04:49,720
do we three look like couples?

60
00:04:50,920 --> 00:04:53,200
Who says flowers are only for couples?

61
00:04:53,320 --> 00:04:55,450
I've been selling flowers all my life,

62
00:04:55,720 --> 00:04:58,040
but I've never received any from others.

63
00:04:59,920 --> 00:05:03,320
But I have received a lot of flowers from others.

64
00:05:03,920 --> 00:05:05,720
Those are bad romances.

65
00:05:06,800 --> 00:05:09,330
You've even received rotten peach blossoms?

66
00:05:10,320 --> 00:05:11,560
It's a bad romance,

67
00:05:11,560 --> 00:05:13,090
not a rotten peach blossom.

68
00:05:13,360 --> 00:05:16,090
You are the one receiving rotten peach blossoms.

69
00:05:17,400 --> 00:05:18,200
So,

70
00:05:18,200 --> 00:05:19,800
buy one for yourself

71
00:05:19,920 --> 00:05:21,450
to change your luck in love.

72
00:05:22,040 --> 00:05:23,570
Hey, but I just remembered.

73
00:05:24,320 --> 00:05:25,920
We also sold flowers back then.

74
00:05:25,920 --> 00:05:27,850
Basically everyone would buy one.

75
00:05:28,760 --> 00:05:31,120
But we called them patriotic flowers.

76
00:05:31,120 --> 00:05:32,250
Patriotic flowers.

77
00:05:33,840 --> 00:05:34,880
Not only that,

78
00:05:34,880 --> 00:05:36,880
some girls even put themselves in the newspaper

79
00:05:36,880 --> 00:05:38,520
to offer themselves in marriage.

80
00:05:38,520 --> 00:05:39,280
But

81
00:05:39,280 --> 00:05:40,480
there is a condition.

82
00:05:42,520 --> 00:05:43,880
That all the bride price

83
00:05:43,880 --> 00:05:46,080
must be used to fund the national salvation.

84
00:05:46,080 --> 00:05:49,000
How can someone publish an ad in the newspaper to marry themselves off?

85
00:05:49,000 --> 00:05:51,400
If she doesn't like the person she marries,

86
00:05:51,920 --> 00:05:54,320
won't she regret it for the rest of her life?

87
00:05:55,560 --> 00:05:57,080
I actually think

88
00:05:57,080 --> 00:05:59,159
marrying a patriotic man

89
00:06:00,080 --> 00:06:02,080
is not a bad choice for a lifetime.

90
00:06:08,680 --> 00:06:10,080
Why are you attacking me?

91
00:06:10,080 --> 00:06:11,880
I didn't ask you to publish an ad.

92
00:06:12,080 --> 00:06:13,800
I just asked you to buy a flower for yourself

93
00:06:13,800 --> 00:06:15,660
and support the lady's business.

94
00:06:17,680 --> 00:06:18,280
This story,

95
00:06:18,280 --> 00:06:19,120
you told it.

96
00:06:19,200 --> 00:06:19,600
And the good guy,

97
00:06:19,600 --> 00:06:20,730
you played the part.

98
00:06:21,360 --> 00:06:22,280
It's my first time

99
00:06:22,280 --> 00:06:24,740
spending my own money to buy myself a flower.

100
00:06:29,960 --> 00:06:31,920
Miss, you paid too much.

101
00:06:35,000 --> 00:06:35,520
Ma'am.

102
00:06:35,880 --> 00:06:38,080
This flower

103
00:06:38,080 --> 00:06:39,840
is for you.

104
00:06:41,080 --> 00:06:43,400
I'm so flattered.

105
00:06:43,880 --> 00:06:46,540
It's also my first time giving someone a flower.

106
00:06:47,159 --> 00:06:48,600
Thank you, miss.

107
00:06:55,320 --> 00:06:56,360
Let's go, Yiyi.

108
00:06:57,400 --> 00:06:58,520
Bye, ma'am.

109
00:06:59,080 --> 00:06:59,720
Let's go.

110
00:07:00,320 --> 00:07:01,560
Aren't you getting one?

111
00:07:01,560 --> 00:07:02,490
Buy it yourself.

112
00:07:19,680 --> 00:07:25,480
2025 marks the 80th anniversary of the victory of the Chinese People's War of Resistance Against Japanese Aggression and the World Anti-Fascist War.

113
00:07:25,480 --> 00:07:27,640
Various activities are held nationwide

114
00:07:27,640 --> 00:07:30,700
to commemorate this great moment of national victory.

115
00:08:08,840 --> 00:08:10,120
Having made tremendous sacrifices,

116
00:08:10,120 --> 00:08:11,640
achieved great victories,

117
00:08:11,640 --> 00:08:13,120
and defended human dignity,

118
00:08:13,120 --> 00:08:16,720
we made great historical contributions to rebuilding world peace.

119
00:08:16,720 --> 00:08:20,160
China will firmly defend the victorious outcomes of World War II

120
00:08:20,160 --> 00:08:23,280
and resolutely smash any attempt to alter its history.

121
00:08:25,360 --> 00:08:30,280
China will prevail.

122
00:08:30,360 --> 00:08:31,800
Yaoyao, can you believe it?

123
00:08:31,800 --> 00:08:33,530
We seem to have time-traveled.

124
00:08:34,440 --> 00:08:35,440
It's incredible.

125
00:08:35,440 --> 00:08:36,360
It's true.

126
00:08:36,799 --> 00:08:39,280
I'm so glad I live in an era of peace.

127
00:08:39,559 --> 00:08:42,039
I'm glad we both live in this era of peace.

128
00:08:43,600 --> 00:08:46,440
I used to think freedom was staying up late watching shows

129
00:08:46,440 --> 00:08:47,640
with no one controlling me.

130
00:08:47,640 --> 00:08:48,960
Now I understand.

131
00:08:49,160 --> 00:08:51,820
It was bought with so many lives and sacrifices.

132
00:08:52,360 --> 00:08:53,360
These

133
00:08:53,360 --> 00:08:55,160
are the choices made by history.

134
00:08:55,280 --> 00:08:57,040
And we, too, will eventually become history.
